tray-colored.png — PLACEHOLDER

This PNG is currently a copy of tray.png (white fill, designed for macOS
template rendering). It is used on Windows and Linux where the system tray
does not auto-invert colors.

Please replace with a proper colored/dark variant before shipping. Suggested
workflow:

  1. Edit tray.svg (viewBox "2 4 28 24"), change fill="#ffffff" to a dark
     neutral like "#2d2d2d" or a brand color.
  2. Export to PNG at 64×64 (or higher, e.g. 256×256 for HiDPI).
  3. Save over crates/gui/icons/tray-colored.png.
  4. Delete this README file.

Code reference: crates/gui/src/main.rs — TrayIconBuilder picks this file on
non-macOS platforms via #[cfg(not(target_os = "macos"))].
